ENUGU – A non-governmental organization (NGO), Women Empowerment Education And Peace Building Initiative (WEPBI), has unveiled its plan to deal with issues of violence against women. Briefing journalists on its plan to alleviate pain and poverty among women and girls, the Executive Director of WEPBI, Joy Ijeoma Oguadimma, said “as we all know, violence against women is not new and that’s one of the major reasons why this NGO was created “have being tackling issues of women that are abused by their intimate partners as well as other gender violence. -Advertisement- “Ending violence against women is everyone’s business and all hands must be on deck to tackle gender violence in our society”. WEPBI unveiled the newly launched online media tv called “witness experience” which will serve as a platform to enable women to share their stories Oguadimma assured that the newly launched online TV will be used to address all forms of ways women’s right are being violated as well as offer counselling to traumatized women and girls Oguadimma reiterated the determination of the organization to continue to provide financial support to women in the state especially the rural dwellers to enable the support their families and live a happy life” we have assisted and provided financial support to kick start their business and today they are doing well and happy so we will continue to render helping hands to alleviate poverty among women, According to her, the objectives of WEPBI is to work with women and girls to participate in all decision-making process that advances their rights as well as tackle all gender-related violence among women and girls.